caledonian.d:
a. Of or pertaining to Caledonia or Scotland; Scottish;
   Scotch.
n. A native or inhabitant of Caledonia or Scotland.

canonry.d:
n. pl. A benefice or prebend in a cathedral or collegiate
   church; a right to a place in chapter and to a portion of its revenues;
   the dignity or emoluments of a canon.

capitally.d:
adv. In a way involving the forfeiture of the head or life;
   as, to punish capitally.
adv. In a capital manner; excellently.

cathetus.d:
n. One line or radius falling perpendicularly on another;
   as, the catheti of a right-angled triangle, that is, the two sides that
   include the right angle.
